With the groundbreaking of two new solar power plants at Manesar and Rohtak, total solar power capacity across #MarutiSuzuki facilities will reach 48.15 MWp by FY 2024-25. As a result, over 30% of Company’s power needs are expected to be met through renewable energy.

#MarutiSuzuki inaugurated its 4,500th Service touchpoint nationwide to bring the convenience of seamless service for customers. Reaching closer to customers, the Company added 310 Service touchpoints in the FY 2022-23, and catered to 22.3 million vehicles, highest in a year.

To ensure that the vehicles are not wasted at their end-of-life, all #MarutiSuzuki vehicles are designed for maximum recyclability and recoverability. All vehicles currently being manufactured by the Company are at least 90% recyclable.

“Right from product design to manufacturing processes, and distribution to end-of-life management, #MarutiSuzuki has been making conscious and focused efforts on environment protection and conservation of natural resources.”- Mr. Hisashi Takeuchi, MD & CEO
